              <Comments>The occurrence of both ἀπιστία and {L:πίστις&lt;SDBG:πίστις:000000&gt;} ({D:31.88}) in this expression in {S:04500300300016} may cause certain difficulties in appropriately rendering the meaning in other languages. It may therefore be necessary to spell out in some detail the fuller implications of ἀπιστία and {L:πίστις&lt;SDBG:πίστις:000000&gt;}. Moreover, the question implies a negative response, but the question (since it is rhetorical) can easily be rendered as a strong negative statement, for example, ‘the fact that they were persons who could not be trusted does not mean that God cannot be trusted.’</Comments>
